9. (14 points) Given a positive sequence $\left\{a_{n}\right\}$ satisfies:
(1) $a_{1}=2012$;
(2) $a_{2} 、 a_{3}$ are integers;
(3) The sequence $\left\{n a_{n}-n^{2}\right\}$ is a geometric sequence with a common ratio no greater than 10.
Find the general term formula of the sequence $\left\{a_{n}\right\}$.

soln_description:
According to the problem, we have $a_{4}=2020$, and 
\[
\left\{\begin{array}{l}
a_{n+1} a_{n-2}=2019+a_{n} a_{n-1}, \\
a_{n+2} a_{n-1}=2019+a_{n+1} a_{n}
\end{array} \Rightarrow a_{n+2} a_{n-1}-a_{n+1} a_{n-2}=a_{n+1} a_{n}-a_{n} a_{n-1}\right.
\]
\[
\Rightarrow a_{n-1}\left(a_{n+2}+a_{n}\right)=a_{n+1}\left(a_{n}+a_{n-2}\right) \Rightarrow \frac{a_{n+2}+a_{n}}{a_{n+1}}=\frac{a_{n}+a_{n-2}}{a_{n-1}} \text {. }
\]

Thus, when $n$ is odd, $\frac{a_{n+2}+a_{n}}{a_{n+1}}=\frac{a_{n}+a_{n-2}}{a_{n-1}}=\cdots=\frac{a_{3}+a_{1}}{a_{2}}=2 \Rightarrow a_{n+2}=2 a_{n+1}-a_{n}$;
when $n$ is even, $\frac{a_{n+2}+a_{n}}{a_{n+1}}=\frac{a_{n}+a_{n-2}}{a_{n-1}}=\cdots=\frac{a_{4}+a_{2}}{a_{3}}=2021 \Rightarrow a_{n+2}=2021 a_{n+1}-a_{n}$.
In summary, every term of the sequence $\left\{a_{n}\right\}$ is a positive integer.

