soln_description:
Prove that from the Law of Sines and the Law of Cosines, we have
$$\begin{aligned}
\frac{\sqrt{\sin A \sin B}}{\sin \frac{C}{2}}= & \frac{\sqrt{\sin A \sin B}}{\sin C} \cdot 2 \cos \frac{C}{2}=\frac{\sqrt{a b}}{c} \cdot \sqrt{2(1+\cos C)}= \\
& \frac{\sqrt{2 a b+2 a b \cos C}}{c}=\frac{\sqrt{(a+b)^{2}-c^{2}}}{c}= \\
& \frac{\sqrt{(a+b+c)(a+b-c)}}{c}=\frac{\sqrt{a+b+c}(a+b-c)}{\sqrt{c^{2}(a+b-c)}}
\end{aligned}$$

By the AM-GM inequality, we have $c^{2}(a+b-c) \leqslant\left[\frac{c+c+(a+b-c)}{3}\right]^{3}=\left(\frac{a+b+c}{3}\right)^{3}$, so $\frac{\sqrt{\sin A \sin B}}{\sin \frac{C}{2}} \geqslant \frac{3 \sqrt{3}(a+b-c)}{a+b+c}$. Similarly,
$$\begin{array}{l}
\frac{\sqrt{\sin B \sin C}}{\sin \frac{A}{2}} \geqslant \frac{3 \sqrt{3}(b+c-a)}{a+b+c} \\
\frac{\sqrt{\sin C \sin A}}{\sin \frac{B}{2}} \geqslant \frac{3 \sqrt{3}(c+a-b)}{a+b+c}
\end{array}$$

Adding the above three inequalities, we get
$$\frac{\sqrt{\sin A \sin B}}{\sin \frac{C}{2}}+\frac{\sqrt{\sin B \sin C}}{\sin \frac{A}{2}}+\frac{\sqrt{\sin C \sin A}}{\sin \frac{B}{2}} \geqslant 3 \sqrt{3}$$

